{"TopicId":180598,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"A shortcut to lock brakes","CreatedByName":"Challyss","CreatedById":189162,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T01:53:34Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Challyss","CreatedById":189162,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T01:53:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIsn\u0027t there a new version coming ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t we just love playing with shortcuts instead of clicking ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWouldn\u0027t it.... make sense ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRead the title again !\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, let me ask you this question. Would a shortcut to toggle brakes be welcome ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWould it be.... difficult to implement ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpam this topic to gain my unconditional love (did you see the irony here ?) !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T05:39:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022Altimeter_GUI_expanded.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u002296\u0022 src=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/images/5/5d/Altimeter_GUI_expanded.png\u0022 width=\u0022270\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe three buttons on the side of the altimeter correspond to toggling lights, gear, and brakes. By clicking the brakes button, it toggles and holds the brakes until you press B or click the button again to disable it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mattinoz","CreatedById":118580,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T05:54:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnless you\u0027re in the Mac version. In that case the only way to lock brakes on is warp while the holding the B key and completely stopped.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a version quirk, we get quit from anywhere. Windows gets brakes that work.*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"razark","CreatedById":32993,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T06:09:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223505184\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221544852356\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103726\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ZooNamedGames\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n29 minutes ago, ZooNamedGames said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy clicking the brakes button...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E explicitly said it wanted a key, not to click.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T06:17:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223505186\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221544853298\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022118580\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mattinoz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, mattinoz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s a version quirk, we get quit from anywhere. Windows gets brakes that work.*\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hate to tell you but we can quit from anywhere too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d love it if there was a way to turn brakes on full without clicking. Alt-B? Does that do anything? Can\u0027t do shift-B that would be like doing a burnout or something \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OHara","CreatedById":162784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T06:29:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother workaround\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhold- B \u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nescape (to pause)\u003Cbr\u003E\nrelease B\u003Cbr\u003E\nescape (to un-pause)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nalt-B (generally, mod-B) would be nice and fit the KSP pattern reasonably well\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Challyss","CreatedById":189162,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T14:29:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223505184\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221544852356\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022103726\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ZooNamedGames\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, ZooNamedGames said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe three buttons on the side of the altimeter correspond to toggling lights, gear, and brakes. By clicking the brakes button, it toggles and holds the brakes until you press B or click the button again to disable it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know clicks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223505193\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221544854198\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002232993\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022razark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, razark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E explicitly said it wanted a key, not to click.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGive this Kerbal a cookie\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223505201\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221544855375\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022162784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022OHara\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, OHara said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnother workaround\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhold- B \u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nescape (to pause)\u003Cbr\u003E\nrelease B\u003Cbr\u003E\nescape (to un-pause)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nalt-B (generally, mod-B) would be nice and fit the KSP pattern reasonably well\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know about this but it\u0027s so barbaric ! Something like Alt B or a configurable key.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-12-15T14:31:14Z\u0022 title=\u002212/15/2018 02:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 15, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Challyss\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T14:47:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222p1n5v.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022499\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgflip.com/2p1n5v.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022888\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*cough* In case that wasn\u0027t enough of a hint, you can assign the brakes on any wheels to any of the custom action groups, and it will toggle them on/off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-12-15T15:21:53Z\u0022 title=\u002212/15/2018 03:21  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 15, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Rocket In My Pocket\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xurkitree","CreatedById":187694,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T15:29:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223505301\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221544885278\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154640\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rocket In My Pocket\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n40 minutes ago, Rocket In My Pocket said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00222p1n5v.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022499\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgflip.com/2p1n5v.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022888\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*cough* In case that wasn\u0027t enough of a hint, you can assign the brakes on any wheels to any of the custom action groups, and it will toggle them on/off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut what if its an Science \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E SSTA with Radiators and Landing Gear as legs? Just to use all the functions on the craft will require all the stock action groups, then where can I get my permabrake?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI honestly think that it should be a toggle rather than a lever.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T15:38:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223505301\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221544885278\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154640\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rocket In My Pocket\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n50 minutes ago, Rocket In My Pocket said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*cough* In case that wasn\u0027t enough of a hint, you can assign the brakes on any wheels to any of the custom action groups, and it will toggle them on/off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs the original author of a mod that specifically circumvented the entire action group paradigm due to the fact that I kept forgetting to assign them in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E (and didn\u0027t like the mods that allowed assigning them in flight) this is as useful as mentioning after jumping out of the plane that I could have put on a parachute.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, it\u0027s super clunky and prone to forgetting SOME wheels but not all of them. Just having a key (combo) is far better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-12-15T15:39:06Z\u0022 title=\u002212/15/2018 03:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 15, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by 5thHorseman\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T15:53:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223505324\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221544887797\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187694\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Xurkitree\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n18 minutes ago, Xurkitree said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut what if its an Science \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E SSTA with Radiators and Landing Gear as legs? Just to use all the functions on the craft will require all the stock action groups, then where can I get my permabrake?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI honestly think that it should be a toggle rather than a lever.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere are 10 custom action groups, more with mods; I\u0027m sure you can spare one of those for the brakes *if* having a keyboard toggle is so important to you. If it isn\u0027t, just use the UI button provided.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223505329\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221544888281\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 minutes ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs the original author of a mod that specifically circumvented the entire action group paradigm due to the fact that I kept forgetting to assign them in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E (and didn\u0027t like the mods that allowed assigning them in flight) this is as useful as mentioning after jumping out of the plane that I could have put on a parachute.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, it\u0027s super clunky and prone to forgetting SOME wheels but not all of them. Just having a key (combo) is far better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, yeah; it could be better of course, most things could lol. It is an available stock solution to the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0027s problem though. He asked for a keyboard toggle for brakes, and I gave him one! Please though, hold your applause and remember to tip your waitress!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Xurkitree","CreatedById":187694,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T15:58:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223505336\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221544889201\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154640\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rocket In My Pocket\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Rocket In My Pocket said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n[snip]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022giphy.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022214\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.giphy.com/media/lI6nHr5hWXlu0/giphy.gif\u0022 width=\u0022301\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Rocket In My Pocket","CreatedById":154640,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-15T16:11:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMostly on topic here:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA rather curious thing is that I can\u0027t see any difference between the brakes group and the other two UI toggle groups in the .cfg, yet for some reason the brakes group needs to be held down when using the keyboard.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLANDING_GEAR\u003Cbr\u003E\n{\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0primary = G\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0secondary = JoystickButton9\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0group = 0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0modeMask = -1\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0modeMaskSec = -1\u003Cbr\u003E\n}\u003Cbr\u003E\nHEADLIGHT_TOGGLE\u003Cbr\u003E\n{\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0primary = U\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0secondary = None\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0group = 0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0modeMask = -1\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0modeMaskSec = -1\u003Cbr\u003E\n}\u003Cbr\u003E\nBRAKES\u003Cbr\u003E\n{\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0primary = B\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0secondary = Mouse3\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0group = 0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0modeMask = -1\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\u00A0 \u00A0modeMaskSec = -1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if there is any way to get it to work as a toggle on the keyboard via \u0022B\u0022 by mucking with this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-18T00:19:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223505336\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221544889201\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154640\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rocket In My Pocket\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/15/2018 at 10:53 AM, Rocket In My Pocket said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m sure you can spare one of those for the brakes\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNobody uses abort on rovers anyways....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-18T01:34:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223506596\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221545092355\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNobody uses abort \u003Cs\u003Eon rovers\u003C/s\u003E anyways....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFixed that for you \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EBefore All Y\u0027All (the mod not you all here in this thread) Abort was frequently my \u0022open all solar panels\u0022 action group. And recently I\u0027ve started actually setting it up as I\u0027m trying out that whole no-revert thing.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-12-18T01:37:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223506641\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022180598\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221545096867\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u00225thHorseman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, 5thHorseman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFixed that for you \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI use a part failure mod, so I do require myself to setup abort plans for manned missions.\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"severedsolo","CreatedById":80345,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-01-06T09:34:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m definitely in favour of this as a stock thing - but for now there is a mod for that (check DoubleTapBrakes in my sig).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIncidentally - I\u0027m 99% sure this used to be a stock thing, I swear I remember that double tabbing \u0022B\u0022 in earlier versions would lock the parking brake (I\u0027m talking ancient versions here, 0.18 or so) - I actually found a little \u0022bug\u0022 when coding DoubleTapBrakes - at first I tried to use the function that was \u0022double tap key \u003Cem\u003Edown\u003C/em\u003E\u0022 and it wouldn\u0027t work, then I tried \u0022double tap key \u003Cem\u003Eup\u0022\u003C/em\u003E and it did.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI wonder if that function is still there, but coded to \u0022key down\u0022 which is why it doesn\u0027t work (maybe due to an obscure stock bug)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}